This paper is primarily focused on the relationship between self-attention and convolutional layers in the context of computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of attention mechanisms in deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also analyzes the expressiveness of self-attention layers, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of attention mechanisms in natural language processing, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
